---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PaintedHighlight from "../components/PaintedHighlight.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-[820px] px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <p class="label-mono mb-10">erlonrachi.com / signature component / v0.1</p>

    <h1 class="display-xl mb-14">
      The <PaintedHighlight>painted highlight</PaintedHighlight>
    </h1>

    <p class="measure mb-20" style="color: var(--paper-soft); font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.65;">
      Three proportional variants of the same gesture. EU Mustard Gold over Europa Blue. Used sparingly: one per section, two maximum above the fold. The brush stroke marks the single point a paragraph is built to deliver, and nothing else.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-24">
      <p class="label-mono mb-5">Variant 1 / single word</p>
      <p class="display-lg">
        Erlon is from <PaintedHighlight>Europa</PaintedHighlight>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20">
      <p class="label-mono mb-5">Variant 2 / short phrase</p>
      <p class="display-lg">
        His thesis is <PaintedHighlight>building people before code</PaintedHighlight>, and it travels.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20">
      <p class="label-mono mb-5">Variant 3 / short line</p>
      <p class="display-lg">
        He follows a single rule: <PaintedHighlight>data and knowledge are more important than software</PaintedHighlight>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-24">
      <p class="label-mono mb-5">Wrap behavior / multi-stroke across lines</p>
      <p class="measure" style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.55;">
        Erlon's working thesis is that <PaintedHighlight>data and knowledge are more important than the software that processes them</PaintedHighlight>, and most enterprise AI failures come from inverting that order.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-24">
      <p class="label-mono mb-5">In body context / smaller type</p>
      <p class="measure" style="color: var(--paper-soft);">
        Every page passes one test: could this be sent to a senior buyer or a recruiter without apology? The answer requires <PaintedHighlight>premium by subtraction</PaintedHighlight>, not by additions. Strip until nothing else can come out, then ship.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20">
      <p class="label-mono mb-5">For comparison / same prose, no highlight</p>
      <p class="measure" style="color: var(--paper-soft);">
        Every page passes one test: could this be sent to a senior buyer or a recruiter without apology? The answer requires premium by subtraction, not by additions. Strip until nothing else can come out, then ship.
      </p>
    </section>

    <footer class="mt-32 pt-10" style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(230,228,218,0.12);">
      <p class="label-mono">painted-highlight v0.1 / brief at briefs/painted-highlight.brief.md</p>
      <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--paper-muted); font-size: 14px;">
        Next pass refines: SVG path character (endpoint taper, edge irregularity), exact hex against locked Europa Blue surface, second splash variant if needed.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>
